  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether maintenance therapy with oral AP23573
      (ridaforolimus), by preventing and controlling tumor growth for a prolonged period of time in
      patients with metastatic soft-tissue or bone sarcomas responding to chemotherapy, will result
      in clinically significant improvement in progression-free survival as compared to oral
      placebo.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
